title: Arnold Bax - Sym No 5 - V Handley, BBC Philc (2003) [Philidor]
description:
A latterday Romantic, Arnold Bax lost ground in the 1950s, as the British critical establishment sought to promote more recent musical trends to gain ground abroad. Bax's rhapsodic genius and brilliant sense of orchestration eventually won him new audiences in the 1980s and 1990s. His Fifth Symphony remains among his most popular, both for its strength of form and its highly romantic, personalized content.

Bio and images included.
